  "text": "The hot restart mechanism in Envoy is a sophisticated process for performing live upgrades without service interruption. The implementation involves the following key components:\n\n## HotRestart Interface (envoy/server/hot_restart.h)\nDefines the abstract HotRestart interface with methods for:\n- `drainParentListeners()`: Shutdown parent listeners to begin graceful draining\n- `duplicateParentListenSocket()`: Retrieve listening sockets from parent process via Unix domain socket file descriptor passing\n- `registerUdpForwardingListener()`: Register UDP listeners for QUIC packet forwarding from parent to child\n- `parentDrainedCallbackRegistrar()`: Get interface for registering callbacks when parent is drained\n- `sendParentAdminShutdownRequest()`: Request parent to shutdown admin functionality\n- `sendParentTerminateRequest()`: Signal parent process to terminate\n- `mergeParentStatsIfAny()`: Merge parent statistics into child's stats store\n- `initialize()`: Initialize parent/child logic after startup\n\n## HotRestartImpl (source/server/hot_restart_impl.h, .cc)\nThe main Linux implementation that:\n- Creates or attaches to a shared memory segment (named via `/envoy_shared_memory_{base_id}`) containing `SharedMemory` struct\n- Initializes process-shared pthread mutexes (`ProcessSharedMutex`) for logging and access log synchronization\n- Manages both parent and child aspects via `HotRestartingParent` and `HotRestartingChild` instances\n- Calls `attachSharedMemory()` to manage shared memory lifecycle with version checking (HOT_RESTART_VERSION)\n- Sets `PR_SET_PDEATHSIG` to ensure child terminates if parent dies unexpectedly\n- Delegates to child/parent for actual handshake and socket passing\n\n## Shared Memory and Synchronization\nThe `SharedMemory` struct stores:\n- `size_` and `version_`: For compatibility checking between processes\n- `log_lock_` and `access_log_lock_`: Process-shared pthread mutexes\n- `flags_`: Atomic flags including `SHMEM_FLAGS_INITIALIZING` to prevent simultaneous initialization\n\n## Parent/Child Handshake (HotRestartingBase)\nBoth parent and child inherit from `HotRestartingBase` which provides:\n- `RpcStream` class: Manages Unix domain socket communication using SOCK_DGRAM (datagram mode) for atomic message delivery\n- Socket binding via `bindDomainSocket()` with naming scheme: `{socket_path}_{role}_{base_id}`\n- Two separate RPC streams: main stream for control messages, UDP forwarding stream for QUIC packet forwarding\n- Protocol: Length-prefixed protobuf messages sent via `sendmsg()` with ancillary data for file descriptor passing (CMSG_RIGHTS)\n\n## Parent Process (HotRestartingParent in source/server/hot_restarting_parent.h, .cc)\nHandles requests from child:\n- Creates two domain sockets: one for main RPC, one for UDP forwarding\n- `initialize()`: Registers socket event handler on dispatcher for receiving child requests\n- `onSocketEvent()`: Processes incoming `HotRestartMessage::Request` from child\n- Request handling via `Internal` class:\n  - `getListenSocketsForChild()`: Looks up listener by address, extracts listening socket fd, passes via SCM_RIGHTS\n  - `exportStatsToChild()`: Exports gauges and counters with latched values and dynamic span information\n  - `drainListeners()`: Initiates graceful drain with UDP packet handler for forwarding undeliverable QUIC packets\n  - `shutdownAdmin()`: Shuts down parent's admin interface so child can take over\n- Increments `hot_restart_generation` gauge for tracking generations\n\n## Child Process (HotRestartingChild in source/server/hot_restarting_child.h, .cc)\nRequests from parent and manages readiness:\n- Creates domain sockets with addresses derived from restart_epoch (0 = first process, 1 = second, etc., cycling mod 3)\n- `initialize()`: Optionally tests connection to parent; if no parent and `skip_hot_restart_on_no_parent` is set, proceeds as standalone\n- `duplicateParentListenSocket()`: Sends request message, blocks receiving response with file descriptor\n- `drainParentListeners()`: Sends drain request (no reply expected), marks child ready to receive traffic\n- `getParentStats()`: Sends stats request, receives protobuf with gauge values, counter deltas, and dynamic spans\n- `mergeParentStats()`: Creates `StatMerger` to merge parent stats while handling scope-based temporaries\n- `sendParentAdminShutdownRequest()`: Requests parent shutdown admin, receives original start time\n- `sendParentTerminateRequest()`: Signals parent to terminate, cleans up stat merger\n- `registerParentDrainedCallback()`: Registers callbacks for UDP listeners that wait for parent drain\n- `onSocketEventUdpForwarding()`: Receives forwarded QUIC UDP packets from parent during drain\n- `UdpForwardingContext`: Maps listener addresses to listener configs for packet routing\n\n## Protocol Buffers (source/server/hot_restart.proto)\nDefines `HotRestartMessage` with:\n- Request types: `PassListenSocket`, `ShutdownAdmin`, `Stats`, `DrainListeners`, `Terminate`, `ForwardedUdpPacket`, `TestConnection`\n- Reply types: `PassListenSocket` (with fd via control message), `ShutdownAdmin`, `Stats` (with gauges, counter deltas, dynamics)\n- Embedded message structures for multi-chunk protobuf transmission (up to 4096 bytes per datagram)\n\n## OS System Calls (envoy/api/os_sys_calls_hot_restart.h)\nAbstract interface for hot restart specific system calls:\n- `shmOpen()`: Wrapper around `shm_open()` for creating/opening shared memory\n- `shmUnlink()`: Wrapper for `shm_unlink()` to remove shared memory objects\n\n## Implementation (source/common/api/posix/os_sys_calls_impl_hot_restart.cc)\nPOSIX implementation with `HotRestartOsSysCallsSingleton` for single-threaded access.\n\n## Drain Sequence\n1. Child calls `drainParentListeners()` after initialization completes\n2. Parent receives `DrainListeners` request and calls `server_->drainListeners()` with `NonDispatchedUdpPacketHandler`\n3. Parent begins closing listeners and draining existing connections\n4. Child registers UDP forwarding listeners via `registerUdpForwardingListener()`\n5. UDP packets not matching parent connections are forwarded to child via UDP forwarding RPC stream\n6. Child's `onSocketEventUdpForwarding()` routes packets to appropriate worker via `listenerWorkerRouter`\n7. After drain timeout, parent terminates\n\n## Child Readiness Signaling\nChild readiness is signaled through:\n- `drainParentListeners()` call indicates child is ready to receive new traffic\n- Shared memory `flags_` with `SHMEM_FLAGS_INITIALIZING` cleared once child is fully initialized\n- Parent drain completion triggers registered callbacks via `registerParentDrainedCallback()`\n- Generation counter increment in shared memory tracks successive hot restarts\n\nThis architecture enables zero-downtime updates by coordinating socket handoff, stats merging, and graceful listener drain between parent and child processes using Unix domain sockets and shared memory primitives."
}
